This topic explains how to install <%= vars.ops_manager %> on AWS using Terraform.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

After you install <%= vars.ops_manager %> on AWS using Terraform,
you can install either the <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) or
<%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>) runtime on the <%= vars.ops_manager %>.

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](../aws/config-terraform.html).

## <a id="terraform-pks"></a> Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform

To install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy <%= vars.ops_manager %>. For more information, see [Deploying <%= vars.ops_manager %> on AWS Using Terraform](../aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. For more information, see [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](../aws/config-terraform.html).

